snippet.textDisplay:
Writing "Damaged" on your forehead violates the "Show don't tell" rule of screenwriting.
Also, the "Damaged" is too on the nose.
In Terminator, Arnold says, "I'll be back."
Arnold doesn't say, "I'm going to drive my car through this wall in 2 minutes." because you connect better with the audience when they put it together in their heads.
